ault_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"Summary Post: Yard Management Systems & Yard Workflows Insights","2025-11-28T11:35:57.241Z","2026-03-27T17:22:12.716Z","2026-03-27T17:22:12.749Z",117310084099155,{"_uid":1934,"body":1935,"link":3306,"title":1928,"author":3307,"excerpt":3309,"category":3310,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":3311,"seo_image":3312,"seo_title":3314,"button_text":132,"cover_image":3315,"gated_asset":3319,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":3320,"background_color":3321,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"9f50ae69-ae2a-4505-973c-6259d7c3e6df",{"type":66,"content":1936},[1937,1947,1955,1963,2024,2033,2041,2093,2174,2193,2202,2210,2289,2297,2306,2325,2333,2398,2406,2415,2423,2486,2494,2503,2511,2576,2584,2593,2601,2666,2674,2683,2728,2737,2767,2776,2784,2843,2851,2860,2913,2922,2957,2966,2974,3056,3064,3073,3081,3133,3141,3150,3158,3167,3233,3242,3289,3298],{"type":69,"attrs":1938,"content":1939},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[1940],{"text":1941,"type":75,"marks":1942},"The modern yard: from blind spot to control tower",[1943,1946],{"type":149,"attrs":1944},{"color":1945},"#000000",{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1948,"content":1949},{"textAlign":139},[1950],{"text":1951,"type":75,"marks":1952},"For years, the yard was the least digitized link in the supply chain—caught between trucking schedules and warehouse priorities, dependent on phones, clipboards, and good luck. That’s changing fast. When the yard becomes a digital control tower, everything it touches gets easier: trucks stop idling, doors turn faster, detention bills shrink, and the warehouse finally knows what’s actually sitting 200 feet outside its dock doors. Think of this page as a practical field guide to that transformation: how yard management systems (YMS) work, how they snap into WMS/TMS, where automation actually pays off, and which policies and metrics prevent chaos from creeping back in.",[1953],{"type":149,"attrs":1954},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":1956,"content":1957},{"textAlign":139},[1958],{"text":1959,"type":75,"marks":1960},"As a yard-tech team that builds AI-native workflows, we sometimes describe the goal this way: turn gates, lots, and docks into a single, observable system that makes decisions as well as it measures them. The software matters, but so does the choreography—how people, processes, and partners move together. ",[1961],{"type":149,"attrs":1962},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":1964,"content":1965},{"textAlign":139},[1966,1971,1985,1996,2007,2013],{"text":1967,"type":75,"marks":1968},"The sections below provide a summary of varied insights from our blog that walk through that choreography with references to deeper reads like ",[1969],{"type":149,"attrs":1970},{"color":1945},{"text":1972,"type":75,"marks":1973},"Yard Management System: Foster Supply Chain Efficiency, ",[1974,1980,1982,1983],{"type":1975,"attrs":1976},"link",{"href":1977,"uuid":1978,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-management-system-foster-supply-chain-efficiency-today","f17dfcdd-ae77-4228-a1f9-39762bda64c2","_self",{"type":149,"attrs":1981},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},"underline",{"text":1986,"type":75,"marks":1987},"Yard Management Software: Elevate Logistics Efficiency, ",[1988,1992,1994,1995],{"type":1975,"attrs":1989},{"href":1990,"uuid":1991,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-management-software-elevate-logistics-efficiency-today","5fc1de6f-79f4-4d51-b3da-88e808120872",{"type":149,"attrs":1993},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":1997,"type":75,"marks":1998},"YMS: Features, Benefits & Innovations, ",[1999,2003,2005,2006],{"type":1975,"attrs":2000},{"href":2001,"uuid":2002,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yms-features-benefits-innovations","376b02d9-aede-4cb7-bbdb-7341f8325472",{"type":149,"attrs":2004},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2008,"type":75,"marks":2009},"and ",[2010,2012],{"type":149,"attrs":2011},{"color":1945},{"type":1984},{"text":2014,"type":75,"marks":2015},"Dynamic Yard Management System: Optimize Supply Chain Visibility.",[2016,2020,2022,2023],{"type":1975,"attrs":2017},{"href":2018,"uuid":2019,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/dynamic-yard-management-system-optimize-supply-chain-visibility","bd8bfbc1-54dc-4576-91f4-e2a2bc66efc1",{"type":149,"attrs":2021},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"type":69,"attrs":2025,"content":2026},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2027],{"text":2028,"type":75,"marks":2029},"What a smart YMS actually does (and what it doesn’t)",[2030,2032],{"type":149,"attrs":2031},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2034,"content":2035},{"textAlign":139},[2036],{"text":2037,"type":75,"marks":2038},"A modern YMS is more than a spreadsheet of trailer slots. It’s a live model of the yard: a shared source of truth for “what’s where,” “what’s next,” and “who needs to know.” At minimum, the system should:",[2039],{"type":149,"attrs":2040},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2042},[2043,2053,2063,2073,2083],{"type":1557,"content":2044},[2045],{"type":112,"attrs":2046,"content":2047},{"textAlign":139},[2048],{"text":2049,"type":75,"marks":2050},"Maintain real-time trailer inventory (location, status, contents/mission).",[2051],{"type":149,"attrs":2052},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2054},[2055],{"type":112,"attrs":2056,"content":2057},{"textAlign":139},[2058],{"text":2059,"type":75,"marks":2060},"Coordinate moves across drivers/spotters with mobile tasking.",[2061],{"type":149,"attrs":2062},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2064},[2065],{"type":112,"attrs":2066,"content":2067},{"textAlign":139},[2068],{"text":2069,"type":75,"marks":2070},"Sync appointments and door availability with a dock scheduler.",[2071],{"type":149,"attrs":2072},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2074},[2075],{"type":112,"attrs":2076,"content":2077},{"textAlign":139},[2078],{"text":2079,"type":75,"marks":2080},"Provide event history to settle accessorials and analyze dwell.",[2081],{"type":149,"attrs":2082},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2084},[2085],{"type":112,"attrs":2086,"content":2087},{"textAlign":139},[2088],{"text":2089,"type":75,"marks":2090},"Integrate with WMS/TMS so the warehouse and transportation teams see the same reality.",[2091],{"type":149,"attrs":2092},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2094,"content":2095},{"textAlign":139},[2096,2101,2112,2117,2124,2129,2138,2147,2153,2158,2169],{"text":2097,"type":75,"marks":2098},"If that sounds simple, it isn’t. Most failures come from partial digitization—only appointments, or only inventory, or only gate cameras—without a consistent workflow engine behind it. To see how these building blocks fit, zoom in on three typical functions:  ",[2099],{"type":149,"attrs":2100},{"color":1945},{"text":2102,"type":75,"marks":2103},"“Yard Management in Warehousing: Drive Efficiency with Automation”",[2104,2108,2110,2111],{"type":1975,"attrs":2105},{"href":2106,"uuid":2107,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-management-in-warehousing-drive-efficiency-with-automation","a4e9fce7-c355-4302-85fe-28bd1ac63208",{"type":149,"attrs":2109},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2113,"type":75,"marks":2114}," (yard ",[2115],{"type":149,"attrs":2116},{"color":1945},{"text":2118,"type":75,"marks":2119},"⇆",[2120,2123],{"type":149,"attrs":2121},{"color":2122},"#555555",{"type":710},{"text":2125,"type":75,"marks":2126}," warehouse boundaries),",[2127],{"type":149,"attrs":2128},{"color":1945},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":2130},[2131,2135,2137],{"type":1975,"attrs":2132},{"href":2133,"uuid":2134,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-dock-management-boost-efficiency-with-ai-and-yms-solutions","83b7b92e-d879-4693-a56c-3249ecdabc0f",{"type":149,"attrs":2136},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":2139,"type":75,"marks":2140},"“Yard Dock Management: Boost Efficiency with AI and YMS Solutions”",[2141,2143,2145,2146],{"type":1975,"attrs":2142},{"href":2133,"uuid":2134,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2144},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":2148},[2149,2151],{"type":1975,"attrs":2150},{"href":2133,"uuid":2134,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2152},{"color":1945},{"text":2154,"type":75,"marks":2155},"(turning doors, not just booking them), and ",[2156],{"type":149,"attrs":2157},{"color":1945},{"text":2159,"type":75,"marks":2160},"“Yard Asset Management: Digitize Logistics for Efficiency”",[2161,2165,2167,2168],{"type":1975,"attrs":2162},{"href":2163,"uuid":2164,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-asset-management-digitize-logistics-for-efficiency","d2884aeb-8b62-4ed9-b6c7-f8a75586f419",{"type":149,"attrs":2166},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2170,"type":75,"marks":2171}," (tight control of trailer, chassis, and container assets). ",[2172],{"type":149,"attrs":2173},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2175,"content":2176},{"textAlign":139},[2177,2182,2188],{"text":2178,"type":75,"marks":2179},"What a YMS does ",[2180],{"type":149,"attrs":2181},{"color":1945},{"text":2183,"type":75,"marks":2184},"not",[2185,2187],{"type":149,"attrs":2186},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":2189,"type":75,"marks":2190}," do: it doesn’t replace your WMS or TMS. It makes both more accurate and more timely by eliminating the “yard fog” that creates surprises at doors and missed updates in transit.",[2191],{"type":149,"attrs":2192},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2194,"content":2195},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2196],{"text":2197,"type":75,"marks":2198},"The integration spine: YMS - WMS - TMS ",[2199,2201],{"type":149,"attrs":2200},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2203,"content":2204},{"textAlign":139},[2205],{"text":2206,"type":75,"marks":2207},"The fastest path to ROI is integration. When your YMS and WMS talk, put-away and picking don’t stall because a trailer quietly moved across the lot. When YMS and TMS talk, the appointment book reflects reality and status updates don’t lag. And when computer vision feeds the YMS, you stop arguing about whether something arrived—you can prove when and where it crossed the line.",[2208],{"type":149,"attrs":2209},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2211},[2212,2239,2255],{"type":1557,"content":2213},[2214],{"type":112,"attrs":2215,"content":2216},{"textAlign":139},[2217,2223,2228],{"text":2218,"type":75,"marks":2219},"YMS + WMS:",[2220,2222],{"type":149,"attrs":2221},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":2224,"type":75,"marks":2225}," Remove “door surprise.” If the WMS expects Trailer 104 at Door 6, the YMS ensures the move actually happens on time—or raises an exception. See ",[2226],{"type":149,"attrs":2227},{"color":1945},{"text":2229,"type":75,"marks":2230},"“YMS and WMS Integration: Augment Efficiency in Supply Chain.”",[2231,2235,2237,2238],{"type":1975,"attrs":2232},{"href":2233,"uuid":2234,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yms-and-wms-integration-auigment-efficiency-in-supply-chain","c65a8cde-4598-47ca-81b5-d6b99e6eef35",{"type":149,"attrs":2236},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"type":1557,"content":2240},[2241],{"type":112,"attrs":2242,"content":2243},{"textAlign":139},[2244,2250],{"text":2245,"type":75,"marks":2246},"YMS + TMS:",[2247,2249],{"type":149,"attrs":2248},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":2251,"type":75,"marks":2252}," Keep carrier ETAs, statuses, and detention clocks honest.",[2253],{"type":149,"attrs":2254},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2256},[2257],{"type":112,"attrs":2258,"content":2259},{"textAlign":139},[2260,2266,2275,2284],{"text":2261,"type":75,"marks":2262},"Computer Vision:",[2263,2265],{"type":149,"attrs":2264},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":2267},[2268,2272,2274],{"type":1975,"attrs":2269},{"href":2270,"uuid":2271,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/trailer-tracking-systems-features-benefits-fleet-tips","5f914a97-4c44-4c57-bdba-e0deb206336f",{"type":149,"attrs":2273},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":2276,"type":75,"marks":2277},"Trailer Tracking Systems: Features, Benefits & Fleet Tips",[2278,2280,2282,2283],{"type":1975,"attrs":2279},{"href":2270,"uuid":2271,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2281},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2285,"type":75,"marks":2286}," shows how GPS, cellular, and IoT data paint the broad strokes; CV confirms plate/asset IDs and conditions where it matters.",[2287],{"type":149,"attrs":2288},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2290,"content":2291},{"textAlign":139},[2292],{"text":2293,"type":75,"marks":2294},"The trick is choosing a single system to reconcile conflicting signals. For yard reality, that’s the YMS. If GPS says “on site” but the gate never recorded an entry, trust the gate. If the dock says “completed” but the trailer never left its door, trust the dock event.",[2295],{"type":149,"attrs":2296},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2298,"content":2299},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2300],{"text":2301,"type":75,"marks":2302},"Scheduling that turns doors—not just books them",[2303,2305],{"type":149,"attrs":2304},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2307,"content":2308},{"textAlign":139},[2309,2314,2320],{"text":2310,"type":75,"marks":2311},"Manual appointment scheduling is the slow lane: phone calls, spreadsheets, and sticky notes. Digital schedulers change the game by modeling capacity, constraints, and priority rules. But schedulers alone don’t keep doors turning—only a scheduler ",[2312],{"type":149,"attrs":2313},{"color":1945},{"text":2315,"type":75,"marks":2316},"connected",[2317,2319],{"type":149,"attrs":2318},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":2321,"type":75,"marks":2322}," to the yard’s tasks and assets can do that.",[2323],{"type":149,"attrs":2324},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2326,"content":2327},{"textAlign":139},[2328],{"text":2329,"type":75,"marks":2330},"Three helpful ways to “slice” this topic (each with a different angle you can link):",[2331],{"type":149,"attrs":2332},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2334},[2335,2356,2377],{"type":1557,"content":2336},[2337],{"type":112,"attrs":2338,"content":2339},{"textAlign":139},[2340,2351],{"text":2341,"type":75,"marks":2342},"Digital Dock Scheduling Software: Features & Benefit Guide",[2343,2347,2349,2350],{"type":1975,"attrs":2344},{"href":2345,"uuid":2346,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/digital-dock-scheduling-software-features-benefit-guide","3b48703c-c269-406b-b6ea-4b1bd66bda6a",{"type":149,"attrs":2348},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2352,"type":75,"marks":2353}," — a capability taxonomy (e.g., self-service booking, capacity models, configurable rules, API/EDI integration).",[2354],{"type":149,"attrs":2355},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2357},[2358],{"type":112,"attrs":2359,"content":2360},{"textAlign":139},[2361,2372],{"text":2362,"type":75,"marks":2363},"Dock Scheduling Software: Transforming Loading Dock Operations",[2364,2368,2370,2371],{"type":1975,"attrs":2365},{"href":2366,"uuid":2367,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/dock-scheduling-software-transforming-loading-dock-operations","5ecb2be6-90c4-4edb-9550-a2c60c8a6728",{"type":149,"attrs":2369},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2373,"type":75,"marks":2374}," — operational change: what adoption looks like, KPI deltas, and how communication shifts from ad-hoc to system-first.",[2375],{"type":149,"attrs":2376},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2378},[2379],{"type":112,"attrs":2380,"content":2381},{"textAlign":139},[2382,2393],{"text":2383,"type":75,"marks":2384},"Best Dock Scheduling Software for Efficient Warehouse Operations",[2385,2389,2391,2392],{"type":1975,"attrs":2386},{"href":2387,"uuid":2388,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/best-dock-scheduling-software-for-efficient-warehouse-operations","ab12e636-2c80-49c0-b70a-70a9a1942552",{"type":149,"attrs":2390},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2394,"type":75,"marks":2395}," — selection criteria and evaluation frameworks (carrier UX, analytics, rule flexibility, and YMS/WMS/TMS fit).",[2396],{"type":149,"attrs":2397},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2399,"content":2400},{"textAlign":139},[2401],{"text":2402,"type":75,"marks":2403},"If you run a drop-heavy operation, the scheduler’s job isn’t only time—it's slot orchestration and door-to-yard flow. That’s where a YMS-native scheduler or a tight YMS–scheduler integration earns its keep.",[2404],{"type":149,"attrs":2405},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2407,"content":2408},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2409],{"text":2410,"type":75,"marks":2411},"Gate, security, and compliance: fast can be safer",[2412,2414],{"type":149,"attrs":2413},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2416,"content":2417},{"textAlign":139},[2418],{"text":2419,"type":75,"marks":2420},"“Fast” and “safe” aren’t opposites when access is automated. Good gate design minimizes handoffs, screens exceptions, and leaves a complete audit trail.",[2421],{"type":149,"attrs":2422},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2424},[2425,2445,2466],{"type":1557,"content":2426},[2427],{"type":112,"attrs":2428,"content":2429},{"textAlign":139},[2430,2440],{"text":2431,"type":75,"marks":2432},"Automated Gate Systems: Enhance Security & Efficiency Today",[2433,2436,2438,2439],{"type":1975,"attrs":2434},{"href":2435,"uuid":1730,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/automated-gate-systems-enhance-security-efficiency-today",{"type":149,"attrs":2437},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2441,"type":75,"marks":2442}," focuses on hardware and access control—ANPR/RFID readers, barrier control, credentialing.",[2443],{"type":149,"attrs":2444},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2446},[2447],{"type":112,"attrs":2448,"content":2449},{"textAlign":139},[2450,2461],{"text":2451,"type":75,"marks":2452},"Gate Automation Systems: Boost Security & Efficiency Today",[2453,2457,2459,2460],{"type":1975,"attrs":2454},{"href":2455,"uuid":2456,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/gate-automation-systems-boost-security-efficiency-today","0f9621d7-5e94-4348-9f6e-724f73df119f",{"type":149,"attrs":2458},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2462,"type":75,"marks":2463}," zooms out to the workflow engine—who is allowed to enter, with which trailer, on what mission, and what happens if the system detects a mismatch.",[2464],{"type":149,"attrs":2465},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2467},[2468],{"type":112,"attrs":2469,"content":2470},{"textAlign":139},[2471,2481],{"text":2472,"type":75,"marks":2473},"Gate Security Management: Systems, Tech & Best Practices",[2474,2477,2479,2480],{"type":1975,"attrs":2475},{"href":2476,"uuid":1729,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/gate-security-management-systems-tech-best-practices",{"type":149,"attrs":2478},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2482,"type":75,"marks":2483}," ties it all together with policy: vendor tiers, visitor flows, driver language support, escort rules, and incident response.",[2484],{"type":149,"attrs":2485},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2487,"content":2488},{"textAlign":139},[2489],{"text":2490,"type":75,"marks":2491},"A good litmus test: can you prove, without calling anyone, when Trailer XYZ entered, where it went, what door it hit, and when it left? If not, your accessorials will become arguments.",[2492],{"type":149,"attrs":2493},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2495,"content":2496},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2497],{"text":2498,"type":75,"marks":2499},"Detention, demurrage, and dwell: stop paying to wait",[2500,2502],{"type":149,"attrs":2501},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2504,"content":2505},{"textAlign":139},[2506],{"text":2507,"type":75,"marks":2508},"Waiting is expensive, and the most expensive waiting is the kind you don’t see. Three reads worth linking side-by-side—each with a distinct lens:",[2509],{"type":149,"attrs":2510},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2512},[2513,2534,2555],{"type":1557,"content":2514},[2515],{"type":112,"attrs":2516,"content":2517},{"textAlign":139},[2518,2529],{"text":2519,"type":75,"marks":2520},"Detention Charges in Logistics: Causes, Costs & Reduction Tips",[2521,2525,2527,2528],{"type":1975,"attrs":2522},{"href":2523,"uuid":2524,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/detention-charges-in-logistics-causes-costs-reduction-tips","3cdbc0bb-432a-4324-a9b2-df26c5912bd3",{"type":149,"attrs":2526},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2530,"type":75,"marks":2531}," — general causes (late turns, mismatched appointments, dwell at gate/dock), cost math, and the policy levers that reduce exposure.",[2532],{"type":149,"attrs":2533},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2535},[2536],{"type":112,"attrs":2537,"content":2538},{"textAlign":139},[2539,2550],{"text":2540,"type":75,"marks":2541},"Detention and Demurrage: Key Shipping Fees Explained Clearly",[2542,2546,2548,2549],{"type":1975,"attrs":2543},{"href":2544,"uuid":2545,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/detention-and-demurrage-key-shipping-fees-explained-clearly","0d67fcb0-583a-4aeb-b521-49f6240b4c3b",{"type":149,"attrs":2547},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2551,"type":75,"marks":2552}," — port and container-specific rules; custody lines and the clock you’re actually on.",[2553],{"type":149,"attrs":2554},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2556},[2557],{"type":112,"attrs":2558,"content":2559},{"textAlign":139},[2560,2571],{"text":2561,"type":75,"marks":2562},"Detention in Trucking: Causes, Fees, Impact & Solutions",[2563,2567,2569,2570],{"type":1975,"attrs":2564},{"href":2565,"uuid":2566,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/detention-in-trucking-causes-fees-impact-solutions","c1a23d7a-6346-4748-8d42-bcfb2183b1d7",{"type":149,"attrs":2568},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2572,"type":75,"marks":2573}," — driver-centric realities: grace periods, carrier communication, and adherence.",[2574],{"type":149,"attrs":2575},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2577,"content":2578},{"textAlign":139},[2579],{"text":2580,"type":75,"marks":2581},"Prevention is a systems problem: good appointment design, live yard visibility, and exception workflows that trigger action. If you can document the yard timeline automatically, you can both reduce the charges and win more disputes.",[2582],{"type":149,"attrs":2583},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2585,"content":2586},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2587],{"text":2588,"type":75,"marks":2589},"Automation in the yard: from individual tasks to orchestration",[2590,2592],{"type":149,"attrs":2591},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2594,"content":2595},{"textAlign":139},[2596],{"text":2597,"type":75,"marks":2598},"There’s a difference between adding a handful of bots and running a policy-driven operation that assigns tasks, respects constraints, and learns from exceptions. Consider three escalating perspectives:",[2599],{"type":149,"attrs":2600},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2602},[2603,2624,2645],{"type":1557,"content":2604},[2605],{"type":112,"attrs":2606,"content":2607},{"textAlign":139},[2608,2619],{"text":2609,"type":75,"marks":2610},"Yard Automation: Enhance Efficiency and Safety in Logistics",[2611,2615,2617,2618],{"type":1975,"attrs":2612},{"href":2613,"uuid":2614,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-automation-enhance-efficiency-and-safety-in-logistics","8d6ce2f9-fe0f-4d49-ab8d-c64923cdbea7",{"type":149,"attrs":2616},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2620,"type":75,"marks":2621}," — the “why automation” case: fewer touches, fewer injuries, fewer idle minutes.",[2622],{"type":149,"attrs":2623},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2625},[2626],{"type":112,"attrs":2627,"content":2628},{"textAlign":139},[2629,2640],{"text":2630,"type":75,"marks":2631},"Yard Automation Platforms: Increase Efficiency & Logistics Safety",[2632,2636,2638,2639],{"type":1975,"attrs":2633},{"href":2634,"uuid":2635,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-automation-platforms-increase-efficiency-logistics-safety","02bcca9f-4199-4edd-8242-e47a05e0bcf5",{"type":149,"attrs":2637},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2641,"type":75,"marks":2642}," — a platform view: rules/policies, integrations, and the analytics layer that measures outcomes.",[2643],{"type":149,"attrs":2644},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2646},[2647],{"type":112,"attrs":2648,"content":2649},{"textAlign":139},[2650,2661],{"text":2651,"type":75,"marks":2652},"Yard Management Automation: Increase Supply Chain Efficiency",[2653,2657,2659,2660],{"type":1975,"attrs":2654},{"href":2655,"uuid":2656,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/yard-management-automation-increase-supply-chain-efficiency","5308d271-84b3-47d2-894f-7f6a755166b3",{"type":149,"attrs":2658},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2662,"type":75,"marks":2663}," — process-wide regimen: gate→yard→dock orchestration, automated move assignment, and SLA-aware prioritization.",[2664],{"type":149,"attrs":2665},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2667,"content":2668},{"textAlign":139},[2669],{"text":2670,"type":75,"marks":2671},"Computer vision slots into this as the data plane—accurate plate, asset, and door events provide the ground truth that optimization engines need.",[2672],{"type":149,"attrs":2673},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2675,"content":2676},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2677],{"text":2678,"type":75,"marks":2679},"Drop trailer programs: elasticity without chaos",[2680,2682],{"type":149,"attrs":2681},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2684,"content":2685},{"textAlign":139},[2686,2691,2702,2707,2712,2723],{"text":2687,"type":75,"marks":2688},"Drop programs boost throughput and resilience, but only when the pool is sized and managed deliberately. ",[2689],{"type":149,"attrs":2690},{"color":1945},{"text":2692,"type":75,"marks":2693},"Drop Trailer Programs: Raise Logistics Efficiency & Flexibility",[2694,2698,2700,2701],{"type":1975,"attrs":2695},{"href":2696,"uuid":2697,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/drop-trailer-programs-raise-logistics-efficiency-flexibility","a76fbb44-68da-46ae-badf-2850958378fb",{"type":149,"attrs":2699},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":2703},[2704,2706],{"type":149,"attrs":2705},{"color":1945},{"type":1984},{"text":2708,"type":75,"marks":2709},"walks through the trade-offs: door-turn math, pool sizing, surge buffers, and the role of yard policy. To make it work daily, combine drop programs with disciplined slotting and task orchestration—",[2710],{"type":149,"attrs":2711},{"color":1945},{"text":2713,"type":75,"marks":2714},"Trailer Yard Management: Optimize Logistics with Smart YMS",[2715,2719,2721,2722],{"type":1975,"attrs":2716},{"href":2717,"uuid":2718,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/trailer-yard-management-optimize-logistics-with-smart-yms","4e42b226-bc1c-43b0-a05a-3ede0ebdb6e9",{"type":149,"attrs":2720},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2724,"type":75,"marks":2725}," shows how the YMS keeps pools fresh and door supply matched to the wave plan.",[2726],{"type":149,"attrs":2727},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2729,"content":2730},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2731],{"text":2732,"type":75,"marks":2733},"Facilities beyond the warehouse: inland nodes and multi-party yards",[2734,2736],{"type":149,"attrs":2735},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2738,"content":2739},{"textAlign":139},[2740,2745,2756,2762],{"text":2741,"type":75,"marks":2742},"Not all yards are warehouse yards. ",[2743],{"type":149,"attrs":2744},{"color":1945},{"text":2746,"type":75,"marks":2747},"Inland Container Depots: Boosting Trade & Supply Chain Efficiency",[2748,2752,2754,2755],{"type":1975,"attrs":2749},{"href":2750,"uuid":2751,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},"/blog/inland-container-depots-boosting-trade-supply-chain-efficiency","36dd9823-0dd3-4f6c-ab1b-29263bede3f5",{"type":149,"attrs":2753},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":2757},[2758,2760],{"type":1975,"attrs":2759},{"href":2750,"uuid":2751,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2761},{"color":1945},{"text":2763,"type":75,"marks":2764},"shows how “dry ports” extend maritime processes inland: customs, storage, and transload, often with multiple parties sharing space and data. These yards amplify the need for strict authorization rules, clear event trails, and role-based visibility—without that, accountability blurs.",[2765],{"type":149,"attrs":2766},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2768,"content":2769},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2770],{"text":2771,"type":75,"marks":2772},"Choosing and shaping your YMS: features, benefits, and innovations",[2773,2775],{"type":149,"attrs":2774},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2777,"content":2778},{"textAlign":139},[2779],{"text":2780,"type":75,"marks":2781},"Three “decision support” reads can anchor your selection process:",[2782],{"type":149,"attrs":2783},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2785},[2786,2805,2824],{"type":1557,"content":2787},[2788],{"type":112,"attrs":2789,"content":2790},{"textAlign":139},[2791,2800],{"text":2792,"type":75,"marks":2793},"YMS: Features, Benefits & Innovations",[2794,2796,2798,2799],{"type":1975,"attrs":2795},{"href":2001,"uuid":2002,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2797},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2801,"type":75,"marks":2802}," — use this for your longlist: inventory models, move engines, dock orchestration, scheduler fit, CV support, analytics.",[2803],{"type":149,"attrs":2804},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2806},[2807],{"type":112,"attrs":2808,"content":2809},{"textAlign":139},[2810,2819],{"text":2811,"type":75,"marks":2812},"Yard Management System: Foster Supply Chain Efficiency Today",[2813,2815,2817,2818],{"type":1975,"attrs":2814},{"href":1977,"uuid":1978,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2816},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2820,"type":75,"marks":2821}," — a practical blueprint for the first deployment wave (what to turn on first, how to measure success).",[2822],{"type":149,"attrs":2823},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2825},[2826],{"type":112,"attrs":2827,"content":2828},{"textAlign":139},[2829,2838],{"text":2830,"type":75,"marks":2831},"Yard Management Software: Elevate Logistics Efficiency Today",[2832,2834,2836,2837],{"type":1975,"attrs":2833},{"href":1990,"uuid":1991,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2835},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2839,"type":75,"marks":2840}," — a modernization view: bridging data across TMS/WMS, automating gates and moves, and exposing the KPI cadence leadership needs.",[2841],{"type":149,"attrs":2842},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":2844,"content":2845},{"textAlign":139},[2846],{"text":2847,"type":75,"marks":2848},"When we implement, we prefer “crawl → walk → run → fly.” Start by making the invisible visible (gate + inventory). Then connect scheduling to door execution. Then automate move assignment. Finally, layer advanced analytics and CV-based validations.",[2849],{"type":149,"attrs":2850},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2852,"content":2853},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2854],{"text":2855,"type":75,"marks":2856},"Scheduling vs. reality: keeping the book honest",[2857,2859],{"type":149,"attrs":2858},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2861,"content":2862},{"textAlign":139},[2863,2868,2873,2881,2887,2895,2900,2908],{"text":2864,"type":75,"marks":2865},"No scheduler survives contact with a volatile day unless reality feeds back in. This is where combining the dock book with the yard’s task graph pays off. Appointments that miss their window shouldn’t default to “urgent”—they should re-enter the queue with rules that preserve flow and fairness. The trio of",[2866],{"type":149,"attrs":2867},{"color":1945},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":2869},[2870,2872],{"type":149,"attrs":2871},{"color":1945},{"type":1984},{"text":2341,"type":75,"marks":2874},[2875,2877,2879,2880],{"type":1975,"attrs":2876},{"href":2345,"uuid":2346,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2878},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2882,"type":75,"marks":2883},", ",[2884,2886],{"type":149,"attrs":2885},{"color":1945},{"type":1984},{"text":2362,"type":75,"marks":2888},[2889,2891,2893,2894],{"type":1975,"attrs":2890},{"href":2366,"uuid":2367,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2892},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2896,"type":75,"marks":2897},", and ",[2898],{"type":149,"attrs":2899},{"color":1945},{"text":2383,"type":75,"marks":2901},[2902,2904,2906,2907],{"type":1975,"attrs":2903},{"href":2387,"uuid":2388,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2905},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2909,"type":75,"marks":2910}," lays out how to design that loop.",[2911],{"type":149,"attrs":2912},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2914,"content":2915},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2916],{"text":2917,"type":75,"marks":2918},"Gate to dock traceability: why it matters",[2919,2921],{"type":149,"attrs":2920},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2923,"content":2924},{"textAlign":139},[2925,2930,2938,2944,2952],{"text":2926,"type":75,"marks":2927},"If you can trace a trailer’s journey from the moment it noses up to the gate, through staging, into a door, and back out, two things happen: disputes get simpler and continuous improvement gets faster. That’s also the foundation of continuous detention reduction. Pair ",[2928],{"type":149,"attrs":2929},{"color":1945},{"text":2472,"type":75,"marks":2931},[2932,2934,2936,2937],{"type":1975,"attrs":2933},{"href":2476,"uuid":1729,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2935},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2939,"type":75,"marks":2940}," with ",[2941,2943],{"type":149,"attrs":2942},{"color":1945},{"type":1984},{"text":2451,"type":75,"marks":2945},[2946,2948,2950,2951],{"type":1975,"attrs":2947},{"href":2455,"uuid":2456,"anchor":139,"target":1979,"linktype":19},{"type":149,"attrs":2949},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1984},{"text":2953,"type":75,"marks":2954}," to design a gating model that captures events without slowing the queue.",[2955],{"type":149,"attrs":2956},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":2958,"content":2959},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2960],{"text":2961,"type":75,"marks":2962},"Metrics that change behavior",[2963,2965],{"type":149,"attrs":2964},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2967,"content":2968},{"textAlign":139},[2969],{"text":2970,"type":75,"marks":2971},"You don’t need fifty KPIs—you need the few that make people change what they do. A reliable starter set:",[2972],{"type":149,"attrs":2973},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":2975},[2976,2992,3008,3024,3040],{"type":1557,"content":2977},[2978],{"type":112,"attrs":2979,"content":2980},{"textAlign":139},[2981,2987],{"text":2982,"type":75,"marks":2983},"Gate cycle time:",[2984,2986],{"type":149,"attrs":2985},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":2988,"type":75,"marks":2989}," time from queue arrival → cleared entry.",[2990],{"type":149,"attrs":2991},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":2993},[2994],{"type":112,"attrs":2995,"content":2996},{"textAlign":139},[2997,3003],{"text":2998,"type":75,"marks":2999},"Yard dwell:",[3000,3002],{"type":149,"attrs":3001},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3004,"type":75,"marks":3005}," average & P90 by carrier, load type, and reason codes.",[3006],{"type":149,"attrs":3007},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3009},[3010],{"type":112,"attrs":3011,"content":3012},{"textAlign":139},[3013,3019],{"text":3014,"type":75,"marks":3015},"Door adherence:",[3016,3018],{"type":149,"attrs":3017},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3020,"type":75,"marks":3021}," plan vs. actual start/finish; % of doors turning on plan.",[3022],{"type":149,"attrs":3023},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3025},[3026],{"type":112,"attrs":3027,"content":3028},{"textAlign":139},[3029,3035],{"text":3030,"type":75,"marks":3031},"Move SLA:",[3032,3034],{"type":149,"attrs":3033},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3036,"type":75,"marks":3037}," percent of move tasks completed within policy windows.",[3038],{"type":149,"attrs":3039},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3041},[3042],{"type":112,"attrs":3043,"content":3044},{"textAlign":139},[3045,3051],{"text":3046,"type":75,"marks":3047},"Detention exposure:",[3048,3050],{"type":149,"attrs":3049},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3052,"type":75,"marks":3053}," forecast vs. actual, by driver and equipment type.",[3054],{"type":149,"attrs":3055},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":3057,"content":3058},{"textAlign":139},[3059],{"text":3060,"type":75,"marks":3061},"Publish these as site scorecards and roll them up across locations. When policies change, measure the effect next week—not next quarter.",[3062],{"type":149,"attrs":3063},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":3065,"content":3066},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3067],{"text":3068,"type":75,"marks":3069},"Policy design: small rules, big results",[3070,3072],{"type":149,"attrs":3071},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3074,"content":3075},{"textAlign":139},[3076],{"text":3077,"type":75,"marks":3078},"Most yard friction is policy friction: undefined grace periods, exceptions that depend on who answers the phone, “just-this-once” overrides that become the norm. Write it down and put the policy into the system:",[3079],{"type":149,"attrs":3080},{"color":1945},{"type":1554,"content":3082},[3083,3093,3103,3113,3123],{"type":1557,"content":3084},[3085],{"type":112,"attrs":3086,"content":3087},{"textAlign":139},[3088],{"text":3089,"type":75,"marks":3090},"Appointment commitments by carrier tier.",[3091],{"type":149,"attrs":3092},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3094},[3095],{"type":112,"attrs":3096,"content":3097},{"textAlign":139},[3098],{"text":3099,"type":75,"marks":3100},"Detention grace windows by load type (live vs. drop).",[3101],{"type":149,"attrs":3102},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3104},[3105],{"type":112,"attrs":3106,"content":3107},{"textAlign":139},[3108],{"text":3109,"type":75,"marks":3110},"Staging zones reserved for at-risk freight.",[3111],{"type":149,"attrs":3112},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3114},[3115],{"type":112,"attrs":3116,"content":3117},{"textAlign":139},[3118],{"text":3119,"type":75,"marks":3120},"Auto-escalations when a door sits idle beyond X minutes.",[3121],{"type":149,"attrs":3122},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3124},[3125],{"type":112,"attrs":3126,"content":3127},{"textAlign":139},[3128],{"text":3129,"type":75,"marks":3130},"Security exceptions that require supervisor approval (with a reason code).",[3131],{"type":149,"attrs":3132},{"color":1945},{"type":112,"attrs":3134,"content":3135},{"textAlign":139},[3136],{"text":3137,"type":75,"marks":3138},"When in doubt, let software enforce the simple rules and route the genuinely complex ones to a human—with a full audit trail.",[3139],{"type":149,"attrs":3140},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":3142,"content":3143},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3144],{"text":3145,"type":75,"marks":3146},"People and change: make the right thing the easy thing",[3147,3149],{"type":149,"attrs":3148},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3151,"content":3152},{"textAlign":139},[3153],{"text":3154,"type":75,"marks":3155},"New software only sticks if operators can see the payoff. That means clean handheld flows for spotters and guards, fewer back-and-forth calls for supervisors, and better predictability for the warehouse. Train to the task, not the tool: “how to clear a gate exception,” “how to swap a door assignment,” “how to document a damaged seal.” The faster an operator can complete a task with the right data in hand, the faster your KPI trendlines will move.",[3156],{"type":149,"attrs":3157},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":3159,"content":3160},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3161],{"text":3162,"type":75,"marks":3163},"Common pitfalls (and how to avoid them)",[3164,3166],{"type":149,"attrs":3165},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":1554,"content":3168},[3169,3185,3201,3217],{"type":1557,"content":3170},[3171],{"type":112,"attrs":3172,"content":3173},{"textAlign":139},[3174,3180],{"text":3175,"type":75,"marks":3176},"Partial digitization:",[3177,3179],{"type":149,"attrs":3178},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3181,"type":75,"marks":3182}," Only the scheduler, or only the gate. Fix by sequencing integrations and insisting on end-to-end event coverage.",[3183],{"type":149,"attrs":3184},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3186},[3187],{"type":112,"attrs":3188,"content":3189},{"textAlign":139},[3190,3196],{"text":3191,"type":75,"marks":3192},"Single-source location truth:",[3193,3195],{"type":149,"attrs":3194},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3197,"type":75,"marks":3198}," GPS says “on site,” but the gate disagrees. Choose a reconciliation hierarchy (gate > dock > telematics).",[3199],{"type":149,"attrs":3200},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3202},[3203],{"type":112,"attrs":3204,"content":3205},{"textAlign":139},[3206,3212],{"text":3207,"type":75,"marks":3208},"Unbounded exceptions:",[3209,3211],{"type":149,"attrs":3210},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3213,"type":75,"marks":3214}," “We’ll figure it out later.” Put timers and outcomes on every exception path.",[3215],{"type":149,"attrs":3216},{"color":1945},{"type":1557,"content":3218},[3219],{"type":112,"attrs":3220,"content":3221},{"textAlign":139},[3222,3228],{"text":3223,"type":75,"marks":3224},"KPI overload:",[3225,3227],{"type":149,"attrs":3226},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3229,"type":75,"marks":3230}," Ten dashboards, no decisions. Pick five, assign owners, and review weekly.",[3231],{"type":149,"attrs":3232},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":3234,"content":3235},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3236],{"text":3237,"type":75,"marks":3238},"Implementation playbooks: crawl → walk → run → fly",[3239,3241],{"type":149,"attrs":3240},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3243,"content":3244},{"textAlign":139},[3245,3251,3256,3262,3267,3273,3278,3284],{"text":3246,"type":75,"marks":3247},"Crawl (0–30 days):",[3248,3250],{"type":149,"attrs":3249},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3252,"type":75,"marks":3253}," Digitize the gate and establish basic trailer inventory; integrate with WMS for door visibility. ",[3254],{"type":149,"attrs":3255},{"color":1945},{"text":3257,"type":75,"marks":3258},"Walk (30–90 days):",[3259,3261],{"type":149,"attrs":3260},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3263,"type":75,"marks":3264}," Connect appointments to door execution; roll out mobile tasking; publish a weekly KPI scorecard. ",[3265],{"type":149,"attrs":3266},{"color":1945},{"text":3268,"type":75,"marks":3269},"Run (90–180 days):",[3270,3272],{"type":149,"attrs":3271},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3274,"type":75,"marks":3275}," Automate move assignment and door slotting; add computer vision for plate/asset verification and seal/damage capture. ",[3276],{"type":149,"attrs":3277},{"color":1945},{"text":3279,"type":75,"marks":3280},"Fly (180+ days):",[3281,3283],{"type":149,"attrs":3282},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"text":3285,"type":75,"marks":3286}," Optimize across sites, standardize policies, and use analytics to forecast dwell and detention risk.",[3287],{"type":149,"attrs":3288},{"color":1945},{"type":69,"attrs":3290,"content":3291},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3292],{"text":3293,"type":75,"marks":3294},"How upstream and downstream systems benefit",[3295,3297],{"type":149,"attrs":3296},{"color":1945},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3299,"content":3300},{"textAlign":139},[3301],{"text":3302,"type":75,"marks":3303},"WMS accuracy improves when the right trailer hits the right door on time; TMS accuracy improves when appointments are honored and status flows are trusted. Carrier relationships improve when you can show a neutral timeline of events and pay faster on clean moves. Finance benefits because accessorials stop surprising the P&L. Safety benefits because people spend less time walking yards or improvising around bottlenecks.",[3304],{"type":149,"attrs":3305},{"color":1945},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[3308],"f387dbd2-db85-4847-91d6-0fb8dfab90c6","The modern yard: from blind spot to control tower\nFor years, the yard was the least digitized link in the supply chain—caught between trucking schedules and warehouse priorities, dependent on phones, clipboards, and good luck. \n","blog","Post",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3313},{},"Yard Management Systems & Workflows Insights | Terminal Industries",{"id":3316,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":3317,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3318,"is_external_url":49},117590166267414,"/storyblok/f/337048/678x684/46f09ef3a2/k.webp",{},[],"Browse Terminal Industries' expert insights on yard management systems and workflows—covering automation, dock scheduling, trailer tracking, and AI-powered yard orchestration.",{"value":3322,"plugin":3323},"#ABFF02","storyblok-palette","yard-management-systems-yard-workflows","all-resources/yard-management-systems-yard-workflows","2025-10-15",-1180,[],80887824638261,"401df9ea-d58e-4808-b53f-956f72f3bc3d","2025-12-02T19:10:19.938Z",[],{"name":3334,"created_at":3335,"published_at":3336,"updated_at":3337,"id":3338,"u